<br>
Note 1: Yes, half elves can wear dwarven cultural.  However, bards (of which I know Warchord is one) cannot.  And no half elf (with the possible exception of bards, I honestly don't know) can wear the dwarven deity restricted armor, since the two religions it can be made for are Brell and Bristlebane.  So, Warchord, I believe you are stuck looking for a human smith.<br>
<br>
Note 2: No, I am no longer taking new clients for my &quot;Pay per combine&quot; business.  Frankly, it was taking a great deal of my time, time I no longer wish to give up.  The PPC system tended to eat up large chunks of my day for all but the most prepared (and with the exception of two of all the clients I dealt with, they were ALL unprepared), as I would go over the entire ingredient list with, pointing out what they had not collected.  Add in the precombine time, as well as the running around in Kaladim itself, and it was a time investment I am no longer willing to make.<br>
<br>
The good news is that this armor has dropped drastically in price since PoP came out.  Pieces that I would routinely sell for 6-7k per sheet (which equates to 6-21k per piece), now go for 3-4k per sheet (3-12k).  There are several vendors in the bazaar that offer this armor at these prices, as well as the odd person selling a piece he/she has upgraded past.  Normally at very competitive prices.<br>
<br>
For any that I have disappointed, I am sorry.  There are hopefully more dwarven smiths coming up who will be hungry for cash (as well as willing to invest the time required), and will be willing to take your orders on a per combine basis.  However, that isnot me any longer. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=327031">Pavel Cursebreaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - dorf Paladin<br>
